urchases%20people%20most%20often%20regret%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20they%20found%20to%20be%20most%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e2504132-fe29-4bcd-8339-59fe12c37fe6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20most%20regretful%20purchases%20are%20usually%20%26quot%3Bthings%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20regretful%20purchases%2C%20consumers%20tend%20to%20have%20buyer's%20remorse%20surrounding%20products%20that%20quickly%20depreciate%20in%20value%20or%20have%20little%20sentimental%20value.%20Think%3A%20a%20brand-new%20car%2C%20a%20designer%20handbag%2C%20or%20the%20latest%20tech%20gadget%20you%20%3Cem%3Ehad%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20have%2C%20but%20barely%20use%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20splurges%20people%20regret%20that%20I%20come%20across%20would%20be%20buying%20new%20cars%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Brenton%20Harrison%2C%20CFP%C2%AE%20professional%20and%20financial%20advisor%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newmoneynewproblems.com%2Fhome%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENew%20Money%20New%20Problems%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20with%20it%20is%20you're%20never%20gonna%20get%20what%20you%20paid%20for%20a%20car%20back%20in%20return%2C%20so%20I%20come%20across%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20end%20up%20regretting%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20smaller%20splurges%2C%20like%20late-night%20food%20delivery%20or%20clothing%20hauls%2C%20can%20pile%20up%20and%20leave%20people%20feeling%20unsatisfied.%20There%20comes%20a%20point%20where%20items%20feel%20more%20like%20useless%20clutter%20taking%20up%20space%20than%20meaningful%20additions%20to%20your%20everyday%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20get%20a%20dopamine%20hit%20when%20we%20experience%20something%20new%2C%20like%20when%20the%20package%20arrives%20and%20we%20use%20a%20new%20item%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20but%20then%20the%20dopamine%20wears%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20explains%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.joyinliving.life%2Fabout-me%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJoy%20Slabaugh%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20CFP%C2%AE%20professional%2C%20financial%20therapist%2C%20and%20educator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22182c5191-34cb-45e7-a085-7981f746a03b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESplurges%20that%20are%20worth%20your%20money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20splurges%20come%20with%20buyer's%20remorse%2C%20or%20a%20hefty%20price%20tag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20the%20most%20valuable%20splurges%20are%20experiences%20where%20clients%20get%20to%20connect%20with%20people%2C%20usually%20people%20that%20they%20care%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Slabaugh.%20%26quot%3BThat%20can%20be%20as%20extravagant%20as%20a%20weekend%20in%20Montauk%20with%20their%20family%E2%80%A6%20or%20as%20simple%20as%20they%20made%20a%20cake%20and%20invited%20their%20friends%20and%20family%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarrison%20agreed%20that%20experiences%20tend%20to%20leave%20the%20most%20lasting%20impact.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20you%20wish%20you%20spent%20less%2C%20people%20end%20up%20appreciating%20the%20experience%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20really%20see%20people%20regret%20experiences.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommon%20factors%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Flifestyle-creep%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elifestyle%20creep%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20FOMO%20(fear%20of%20missing%20out)%20can%20lead%20to%20overspending%20on%20things%20that%20feel%20necessary%20in%20the%20moment%20but%20don't%20provide%20lasting%20value.%20Understanding%20what%20makes%20a%20splurge%20truly%20worth%20it%20is%20the%20first%20step%20toward%20spending%20more%20intentionally.%20That's%20why%20learning%20to%20evaluate%20purchases%20through%20a%20lens%20of%20purpose%20and%20personal%20fulfillment%20is%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce93fa50-5861-47cb-80b4-09466d6722b3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20determine%20whether%20a%20splurge%20is%20worth%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDetermining%20whether%20a%20splurge%20is%20truly%20%26quot%3Bworth%20it%26quot%3B%20often%20comes%20down%20to%20personal%20values%20and%20how%20the%20purchase%20fits%20into%20your%20broader%20financial%20picture.%20Financial%20experts%20say%20that%20aligning%20your%20spending%20with%20what%20matters%20most%20to%20you%20can%20determine%20what%20splurges%20are%20most%20worthwhile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20way%20to%20assess%20whether%20something%20is%20worth%20the%20money%20is%20by%20asking%20reflective%20questions%20before%20making%20the%20purchase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20things%20that%20you%20put%20aside%20money%20for%2C%20I%20try%20to%20ask%3A%20'What's%20the%20purpose%20of%20this%3F%20What%20are%20you%20hoping%20to%20get%20out%20of%20this%3F'%26quot%3B%20said%20Harrison.%20%26quot%3BThat%20way%2C%20people%20can%20take%20a%20step%20back%20before%20they%20spend%20and%20have%20a%20better%20perspective%20on%20its%20value.%20Are%20you%20doing%20this%20because%20it%20adds%20value%20to%20your%20life%2C%20or%20because%20of%20FOMO%3F%20It%20might%20not%20make%20sense%20to%20everyone%2C%20but%20it%20can%20still%20make%20sense%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225d32facc-7313-46af-a358-69c24c31507a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBudgeting%20for%20splurges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESplurges%20don't%20have%20to%20eat%20into%20your%20budget%20when%20you%20create%20space%20for%20discretionary%20spending%20within%20it.%20Consider%20setting%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fsavings-accounts-to-save-for-goals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esavings%20accounts%20with%20buckets%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20specific%20goals%20like%20a%20weekend%20getaway%2C%20a%20shopping%20spree%2C%20or%20a%20new%20gadget.%20This%20method